2ï¸âƒ£ git diff: Utilize it for efficient code reviews.
3ï¸âƒ£ .gitignore: Maintain a clean repository.
4ï¸âƒ£ git fetch vs. git pull: Understand when to use each.
5ï¸âƒ£ Branching: Foster collaboration within your team.
6ï¸âƒ£ git stash: Temporarily store changes in a collaborative setting.
7ï¸âƒ£ git cherry-pick: Apply specific commits across branches without merging everything.
8ï¸âƒ£ git rebase: Be cautious of risks on a public branch.
9ï¸âƒ£ Git Hooks: Ensure coding standards are upheld.
